A 45-year-old Ballito woman was arrested for allegedly killing her four-year-old daughter on Wednesday. Police spokesperson Constable Thenjiswa Ngcobo said the mother told the police that her child was being difficult and troubling her and she drowned the child in a bucket full of water until she stopped moving. The child’s hand were also bound with tape. She was certified dead at the scene. Ngcobo said a case of murder was opened for investigation by Umhlali SAPS. The woman is expected to appear before the KwaDukuza Magistrates Court on Thursday. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.